    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>A big part of the reason London can claim to challenge New York as the financial capital of the world is the growth of its hedge fund business, much of it based in the expensive neighborhood of Mayfair. London's share of global hedge fund assets has doubled over the last five years, according to International Financial Services, a London research group.</p>
      </block>
